      "id": "body",
      "label": "Body text",
      "default": "In open air, fabrics work by absorbing sweat and releasing it into the air. Inside a sealed glove there is no air to release into. So the fabric saturates and sits wet against your skin. Asymmetric Layering doesn't absorb on the skin side. The structure routes moisture from skin to outer face — continuously, without saturation. Built for the only environment where this matters."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "footer_text",
      "label": "Footer text",
      "default": "Developed at the Swedish School of Textiles. Supported by Uppsala University and Vinnova."
    },
